.TH EDITINACME 1
.SH NAME
editinacme \- open a file in acme and wait for it to be deleted
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B editinacme
.I file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Editinacme
uses the plumber to open
.I file
in
.MR acme 1
and then waits until the window for that file is deleted before exiting.
It is intended for use as
.B $EDITOR
in environments where
.I acme
is running.
.PP
.I File
is resolved to an absolute path before being plumbed.
.PP
.I Editinacme
reads the
.I acme
log file to detect when the window is closed.
It exits when a
.B del
event for the file appears in the log.
.SH EXAMPLE
Set
.I editinacme
as your editor and open a file for editing:
.IP
.EX
% EDITOR=editinacme git commit
.EE
.PP
Or invoke it directly:
.IP
.EX
% editinacme src/main.c
.EE
.SH SOURCE
.B \*9/bin/editinacme
.SH SEE ALSO
.MR acme 1 ,
.MR plumb 1 ,
.MR acme 4
.SH BUGS
.I Editinacme
prints a harmless
.I "write error: Broken pipe"
message from
.MR 9p 1
when the log connection is closed on exit.
